Insurance companies face data sprawl with disparate systems and¬error-prone manual processes impeding a holistic view of the business and risk exposure. Gaining this insight is critical at a time when the regulatory environment demands businesses improve their risk models and practices.

Using actuarial statistical analysis and modelling based upon Microsoft solutions, insurance companies are able to better identify risks, price¬policies more effectively, understand their liabilities more accurately,¬and optimise their financial positions.

As the pace of global financial services accelerates and speed becomes essential to decision-making, traditional tools are simply too slow. Coupled with massive on-premises server farms being unsustainably expensive, there is a real need for higher computing throughput but with a compelling TCO.

Microsoft analytics solutions enable financial institutions to benefit from cloud computing by reducing capex and facilitating more complex data analysis. Typical scenarios include risk computation and modelling plus predictive analytics through machine learning of data analysis & patterns.

Faced with exponentially increasing volumes of data, it is challenging for financial institutions to translate that data into insight needed to improve customer profitability and retention. To do this effectively, you need deeper insight into the profitability of you customer portfolio and have the ability to visualise that data so it is actionable.

With Microsoft customer and product analytics solutions, you can capitalise on internal and external data to combine profitability, segmentation and customer preference, to gain a complete end-to-end view of the customer.

The emergence of video and call conferencing, directly from your desktop, tablet or phone, coupled with Presence, the ability to see at a glance when someone is available, changes the speed at which people communicate. Meetings take less time to arrange, decisions are made more quickly, and people are more effective.

Span.Text: Interact with citizens the way they want to using traditional and new digital channels, joined up. Staff have the right information at their fingertips to provide personalised and relevant information every time, whatever the channel.

The Government Digital Strategy sets out how government will redesign its digital services to make them so straightforward and convenient that all those who can use them prefer to do so.
Microsoft solutions fulfil many of the requirements needed to support a 'Digital by Default' approach to supplying government transactional services.

Enable easier interaction with applications, provide personalised and relevant experiences that anticipate needs, remember preferences, and adapt to unique work styles, delivering quality citizen services where and when they are needed.

Gain operational efficiencies, reduce costs, and help ensure security through an integrated suite of solutions. By integrating Unified Communications and rich presence into business workflows, latency and delays can be reduced or eliminated. For geographically dispersed teams, group chat can enable efficient, topic-specific, multi-party discussions.

Automate records throughout the document lifecycle. From creation and collaboration to record declaration, policy-driven retention, and finally, document disposal or archiving, our solutions allows users to collaborate and share information securely across boundaries, protect document integrity, and reduce legal risk.
